<figureCitation id="13363FFCFF918849FEE7637DBF9EA07E" box="[326,442,1568,1595]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1665,1691]" captionTargetBox="[306,1327,213,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-82@6.[306,1327,213,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Species of Corthylus with acute spines on declivity or with interstriae 3 curved and serrate (1 of 2). A, B) C. spinosulus, new species, holotype. C–D) C. spinosus Wood, holotype. E, F) C. spinipennis Wood, holotype. G, H) C. senticosus Wood, holotype. Photographs A–B by the author, C–H by S.M. Smith (Copyright National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, D.C., published by permission)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564897/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3 A, B</figureCitation>
