<subSubSection id="C31770F2FF91884DFF616316BC0CA455" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF918849FF616316BFC3A17D" blockId="3.[192,1442,1611,1848]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FF616316BF18A020" bold="true" box="[192,316,1611,1637]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species would key out to couplet 
<quantity id="4CF58E9CFF918849FD586311BD10A020" box="[761,820,1611,1638]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0922" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="in" value="43.0">43 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C5E88FF918849FC9D6316BDE8A023" author="Wood SL" box="[828,972,1611,1638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" pagination="1 - 1356" refId="ref9695" refString="Wood SL. 1982. The bark and ambrosia beetles of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae), a taxonomic monograph. Great Basin Naturalist Memoirs 6: 1 - 1356." type="journal article" year="1982">Wood’s 1982</bibRefCitation>
key along with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF918849FB266311BB69A020" authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" box="[1159,1357,1611,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FB266311BAB3A023" box="[1159,1175,1612,1638]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FB076311BB25A020" box="[1190,1281,1612,1637]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">spinosus</emphasis>
Wood
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13363FFCFF918849FAFF6316BB84A023" box="[1374,1440,1611,1638]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1665,1691]" captionTargetBox="[306,1327,213,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-82@6.[306,1327,213,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Species of Corthylus with acute spines on declivity or with interstriae 3 curved and serrate (1 of 2). A, B) C. spinosulus, new species, holotype. C–D) C. spinosus Wood, holotype. E, F) C. spinipennis Wood, holotype. G, H) C. senticosus Wood, holotype. Photographs A–B by the author, C–H by S.M. Smith (Copyright National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, D.C., published by permission)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564897/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C–D). An additional species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF918849FDB56332BDA1A0CC" authority="Wood (2007: 850)" authorityName="Wood" authorityPageNumber="850" authorityYear="2007" box="[532,901,1646,1673]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipennis">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FDB56332BC07A0CC" box="[532,547,1647,1673]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FD926332BC89A0CD" box="[563,685,1647,1672]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">spinipennis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9C5E88FF918849FD176333BDA1A0CC" author="Wood SL" box="[694,901,1646,1673]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" refId="ref9765" refString="Wood SL. 2007. Bark and ambrosia beetles of South America (Coleoptera: Scolytidae). Monte L. Bean Science Museum; Provo, Utah. 900 p." type="book" year="2007">Wood (2007: 850)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was described from 
<collectingCountry id="F31A63E9FF918849FBDB6332BAD0A0CD" box="[1146,1268,1646,1673]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
after 1982 and would also key to the same couplet (
<figureCitation id="13363FFCFF918849FDF663CCBCB2A0E9" box="[599,662,1681,1708]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1665,1691]" captionTargetBox="[306,1327,213,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-82@6.[306,1327,213,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Species of Corthylus with acute spines on declivity or with interstriae 3 curved and serrate (1 of 2). A, B) C. spinosulus, new species, holotype. C–D) C. spinosus Wood, holotype. E, F) C. spinipennis Wood, holotype. G, H) C. senticosus Wood, holotype. Photographs A–B by the author, C–H by S.M. Smith (Copyright National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, D.C., published by permission)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564897/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
E–F). All three species share the character of large, acute denticles on the elytral declivity. The species described here is larger than the other two, has an elytral declivity that is more gradually rounded in lateral profile, and has proportionately smaller and less acute denticles on the declivity. All three species are known only from their unique 
<typeStatus id="54B69DDBFF918849FD4363A6BD75A150" box="[738,849,1787,1813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">holotypes</typeStatus>
, a female for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF918849FC4D63A6BA58A150" authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="2020" box="[1004,1148,1787,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosulus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FC4D63A6BDD8A150" box="[1004,1020,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FBAA63A6BA58A150" box="[1035,1148,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">spinosulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and males for 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF918849FA8763A6BB84A150" box="[1318,1440,1787,1813]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FA8763A6BB12A150" box="[1318,1334,1787,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FAE463A1BB84A150" box="[1349,1440,1788,1813]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">spinosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF918849FF516243BFAEA17D" authorityName="Wood" authorityYear="2007" box="[240,394,1822,1848]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipennis">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FF516243BF26A17D" box="[240,258,1822,1848]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FEAE6242BFAEA17D" box="[271,394,1823,1848]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">spinipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13363FFCFF918849FE396243BFFDA17D" box="[408,473,1822,1848]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[192,268,1665,1691]" captionTargetBox="[306,1327,213,1632]" captionTargetId="figure-82@6.[306,1327,213,1634]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Species of Corthylus with acute spines on declivity or with interstriae 3 curved and serrate (1 of 2). A, B) C. spinosulus, new species, holotype. C–D) C. spinosus Wood, holotype. E, F) C. spinipennis Wood, holotype. G, H) C. senticosus Wood, holotype. Photographs A–B by the author, C–H by S.M. Smith (Copyright National Museum of Natural History, Smithsonian Institution, Washington, D.C., published by permission)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564897/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF918849FF616214BBA1A1C3" blockId="3.[192,1440,1865,1927]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF918849FF616214BF3FA126" bold="true" box="[192,283,1865,1891]" pageId="3" pageNumber="2">Female.</emphasis>
Length: 
<quantity id="4CF58E9CFF918849FE236214BFCEA121" box="[386,490,1865,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.70 mm</quantity>
, maximum width: 
<quantity id="4CF58E9CFF918849FD656214BD0FA121" box="[708,811,1865,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.14" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="1.14">1.14 mm</quantity>
; length of elytra: 
<quantity id="4CF58E9CFF918849FC546214BA79A121" box="[1013,1117,1865,1892]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.65" pageId="3" pageNumber="2" unit="mm" value="1.65">1.65 mm</quantity>
; length to width: 2.4; elytral length/total length: 0.618; elytral length/width: 1.45. (n = 1). Color dark brown, slightly paler at base of elytra.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7273F1FF96884EFF61631ABCA1A0C6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564892" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4564892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564892/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" startId="4.[192,268,1607,1633]" targetBox="[337,1295,213,1577]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF96884EFF61631ABCA1A0C6" blockId="4.[192,1440,1607,1667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFF61631ABF0CA024" bold="true" box="[192,296,1607,1633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Figure 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF96884EFE8F631ABC5DA024" authority="Blandford" authorityName="Blandford" authorityYear="1904" box="[302,633,1607,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="parvulus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFE8F631ABFDBA024" box="[302,511,1607,1633]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">Corthylus parvulus</emphasis>
Blandford
</taxonomicName>
, female. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFD78631ABCD3A024" bold="true" box="[729,759,1607,1633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">A)</emphasis>
Dorsal habitus. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFC0C631ABDECA024" bold="true" box="[941,968,1607,1633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">B)</emphasis>
Lateral habitus. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFB20631ABAB9A024" bold="true" box="[1153,1181,1607,1633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">C)</emphasis>
Frons and antenna. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF96884EFA20631ABB84A024" bold="true" box="[1409,1440,1607,1633]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">D)</emphasis>
Declivity. All photographs by the author.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF96884EFEA163BBBC6AA1C3" blockId="4.[191,1442,1766,1927]" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">
Frons evenly concave from epistoma to vertex, weakly impressed longitudinally in middle up to a low, blunt elevation at upper level of eyes. Surface shallowly, densely punctured throughout. Vestiture of short, yellowish setae, uniform in length over entire concavity, without longer fringes at the sides or vertex. Antennal club slightly asymmetrical, 1 
<superScript id="7C788E31FF96884EFED06217BF58A11D" attach="left" box="[369,380,1866,1880]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">st</superScript>
suture septate, 2 
<superScript id="7C788E31FF96884EFD926217BC60A11D" attach="left" box="[563,580,1866,1880]" fontSize="6" pageId="4" pageNumber="3">nd</superScript>
marked by an external groove. Well-developed cirrus of reddish-brown setae, not exceeding the width of the club.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7273F1FF97884FFF606315BD35A0C1" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564895" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4564895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564895/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" startId="5.[193,269,1608,1634]" targetBox="[339,1297,213,1577]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF97884FFF606315BD35A0C1" blockId="5.[192,1440,1608,1669]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFF606315BF0DA026" bold="true" box="[193,297,1608,1635]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Figure 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF97884FFE8C6314BC2BA026" authority="Atkinson, 2020" authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="2020" box="[301,527,1609,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosulus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFE8C6314BC2BA026" box="[301,527,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Corthylus spinosulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24A4210FF97884FFDBA6314BC84A026" box="[539,672,1609,1635]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, female holotype. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFCC96315BD58A027" bold="true" box="[872,892,1608,1634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">A</emphasis>
) Dorsal habitus. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFB9B6315BA72A027" bold="true" box="[1082,1110,1608,1634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">B)</emphasis>
Lateral habitus. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFAAC6315BB0EA027" bold="true" box="[1293,1322,1608,1634]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">C)</emphasis>
Frons and antenna. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF97884FFE866337BF62A0C1" bold="true" box="[295,326,1642,1668]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">D)</emphasis>
Declivity. All photographs by the author.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF97884FFEA16399BF1DA167" blockId="5.[192,1441,1732,1927]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Anterior margin of pronotum rounded, unarmed. Asperities low, small, reduced to impressed lines at summit. Disc of pronotum smooth, shining. Shallow punctures widely separated by more than 5x the diameter of punctures.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF97884DFEA16274BAC9A71C" blockId="5.[192,1441,1732,1927]" lastBlockId="7.[191,1441,214,346]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Striae and interstriae on elytral disc not impressed, punctures shallow and confused, without associated setae. Declivity evenly rounded in profile. A well-developed, elevated marginal crest extends from the declivital suture to about interstriae 4, about 10% of the declivital circumference. Striae poorly defined on declivity, with strial and interstrial punctures confused. Declivital interstriae 1 slightly elevated (but not costate) with 5 widely spaced blunt tubercles, these increasing in size posteriorly. Interstriae 2 weakly impressed, punctures confused, with a blunt tubercle near the apical margin. Interstriae 3 weakly elevated, with 4–5 blunt tubercles, these slightly larger than those on interstriae 1. Additional smaller tubercles on interstriae 5 on declivital face.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7273F1FF94884CFF6163DCBB2BA144" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4564897" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4564897" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4564897/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" startId="6.[192,268,1665,1691]" targetBox="[306,1327,213,1632]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8BB22379FF94884CFF6163DCBB2BA144" blockId="6.[192,1441,1665,1793]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFF6163DCBF0CA0DE" bold="true" box="[192,296,1665,1691]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Figure 3.</emphasis>
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF94884CFE0463DCBC34A0DE" authorityName="Erichson" authorityYear="1834" box="[421,528,1665,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFE0463DCBC34A0DE" box="[421,528,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">Corthylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with acute spines on declivity or with interstriae 3 curved and serrate (1 of 2). 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFA2763DCBEF6A0F8" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">A, B</emphasis>
) 
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF94884CFF4363FEBF56A0F8" authority="Atkinson, 2020" authorityName="Atkinson" authorityYear="2020" box="[226,370,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosulus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFF4363FEBED0A0F8" box="[226,244,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFEA063FEBF56A0F8" box="[257,370,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">spinosulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24A4210FF94884CFEDE63F9BC21A0F8" box="[383,517,1699,1726]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFD2163FEBCE4A0F8" bold="true" box="[640,704,1699,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C–D)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF94884CFD6663FEBDA9A0F8" authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" box="[711,909,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosus">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFD6663FEBCFDA0F8" box="[711,729,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFD4763F9BD65A0F8" box="[742,833,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">spinosus</emphasis>
Wood
</taxonomicName>
, holotype. 
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFBA963FEBA64A0F8" bold="true" box="[1032,1088,1699,1725]" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">E, F)</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0D58FAFF94884CFBE763FEBB08A0F8" authority="Wood" authorityName="Wood" authorityYear="2007" box="[1094,1324,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Corthylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinipennis">
<emphasis id="B979FF6BFF94884CFBE763FEBA7CA0F8" box="[1094,1112,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="5">C</emphasis>
